So, by the nature of the wiki there is no record to consult, but the framing trope (cross-outs from a document-altering smart-alek object) has been tried multiple times as a -J and failed.

This is partially because, as Roget says, 1561 already exists and is very good, and cross-outs make things difficult to read. On top of those, as a source of humor, a basic object trying to make itself sound awesome and calling others stupid is a pretty shallow well.

Not trying to jump down your throat. For a first post, it's generally well written, and those are some very fine ruler puns. Seriously, quite good. Just saying, what you're banking on for whimsy or absurdity comes off instead as a rather tired trope. (Anyone else remember the sexy white sphere?)

-1







